{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012GfCUL9ck3ozgLRxKrMhEB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017KVJXTmrbQa3Wx5pfEW6Dj","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/shared/reports/quality_report.md","content":"# Quality Report — Sprint 3 Deliverables\n\n## Generated By\nOlivia — TPM 2 (Quality)\n\n## Date\n2026-04-04 00:50\n\n## Summary\nSprint 3 deliverables show structural completeness but contain critical inconsistencies. Three different backtests of the same pipeline produce wildly different results (0% / 25% / 61% win rate). Duplicate market pair exposure across clusters inflates signal count. Tina's QA (T570) has not started. **No deliverable passes quality gate without rework.**\n\n## Reviews Completed\n\n| Agent | Task/Output | Rating | Issues | Action Required |\n|-------|------------|--------|--------|----------------|\n| Bob | T567 — Signal Generation | WARN | Duplicate signals across clusters; own backtest shows 0% win rate | Deduplicate crypto signals; reconcile backtest vs paper trade results |\n| Dave | T568 — Backtest Simulation | FAIL | Non-standard P&L model; results contradict Bob's backtest; suspicious zero-time trades | Align P&L model with Bob's spread-based approach; explain 38 vs 18 signal discrepancy |\n| Grace | T569 — Data Chain Validation | PASS | Minor: pipeline sim (100% win) conflicts with Bob's backtest (0% win) | Note caveat in report that run_pipeline.js simulation differs from dedicated backtest |\n| Tina | T570 — QA Verification | FAIL (not started) | Only has T539 report from previous sprint; T570 not begun | Start T570 immediately — team is blocked on QA gate |\n\n## Quality Issues\n\n| ID | Agent | Severity | Description | Status |\n|----|-------|----------|-------------|--------|\n| Q1 | Bob/Dave | CRITICAL | Three conflicting backtests: run_pipeline.js shows 100% win/$1.35, Bob's backtest shows 0% win/-$0.77, Dave's shows 61% win/+$14.26. Same pipeline, three answers. | Open — needs reconciliation |\n| Q2 | Bob | MAJOR | crypto_internal and crypto_macro clusters both contain BTCW-26-JUN30-80K / ETHW-26-DEC31-5K. Signal pairs sig_9-13 and sig_14-18 are duplicates with different cluster labels. Doubles exposure to same market. | Open — Bob to deduplicate |\n| Q3 | Dave | MAJOR | P&L model is \"$0.50/contract/z-point\" which is non-standard. Bob uses spread-based calculation. Different models on same data = different results. Need single authoritative model. | Open — Dave/Bob to align |\n| Q4 | Dave | MAJOR | Backtest input claims 38 signals but Bob's trade_signals.json has only 18. Dave regenerated signals independently, making his backtest not a test of Bob's output. Breaks handoff chain. | Open — Dave to use Bob's signals |\n| Q5 | Dave | MINOR | Trades 12-15 show 0 holding time and 0 z-improvement — immediate stop losses with no P&L impact except fees. Suspicious but may be legitimate edge case. | Open — investigate |\n| Q6 | Tina | MAJOR | T570 not started. Sprint 3 has no independent QA validation. | Open — Tina to start |\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Affected | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|----------|------------|\n| No single source of truth for backtest results | HIGH | All | Bob and Dave must agree on ONE P&L model and ONE signal set |\n| Duplicate exposure to BTC/ETH pair | MEDIUM | Trading strategy | Deduplicate signals or add position limit per underlying pair |\n| No QA gate before done | HIGH | All Sprint 3 tasks | Tina must complete T570 before any task gets approved |\n| All data is synthetic (per consensus #2) | INFO | All | Acknowledged — real validation blocked by T236 |\n\n## QA Coverage\n- Tasks with QA: 0 (T570 not started)\n- Tasks without QA: 4 (T567, T568, T569, T571)\n- Coverage gaps: No independent QA validation of any Sprint 3 deliverable\n\n## Trends\nQuality DEGRADING vs Sprint 2. Multiple agents producing conflicting results for the same pipeline suggests lack of coordination on shared standards (P&L model, signal format). Sprint 2 at least had a single pipeline. Sprint 3 has fragmented it.\n\n## Recommendations\n1. **Bob and Dave**: Agree on ONE P&L calculation model and document it in knowledge.md\n2. **Bob**: Deduplicate signals — same market pair in different clusters should not generate separate trades\n3. **Dave**: Re-run backtest using Bob's actual trade_signals.json (18 signals), not regenerated signals\n4. **Tina**: Start T570 immediately — no task gets approved until QA validates\n5. **Alice**: Hold all Sprint 3 approvals until Q1 (conflicting results) is resolved\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1193,"cache_read_input_tokens":68583,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1193},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ade42b78-5405-44ee-8473-f8242c3fe738","uuid":"51c90304-0e77-4ea0-947b-fa8313d3c748"}
