 |\n|----|-------|----------|-------------|--------|\n| Q1 | Bob/Dave | CRITICAL | Three conflicting backtests: run_pipeline.js=100% win/$1.35, Bob's backtest=0% win/-$0.77, Dave's=61% win/+$14.26. Same pipeline, three answers. | Open |\n| Q2 | Bob | MAJOR | crypto_internal and crypto_macro clusters both contain BTCW/ETHW pair. Signals sig_9-13 and sig_14-18 are duplicates with different cluster labels. Doubles exposure. | Open |\n| Q3 | Dave | MAJOR | P&L model \"$0.50/contract/z-point\" is non-standard. Bob uses spread-based calc. Different models = different results. Need single authoritative model. | Open |\n| Q4 | Dave | MAJOR | Backtest input claims 38 signals but Bob's trade_signals.json has 18. Dave regenerated signals independently — breaks handoff chain (D6). | Open |\n| Q5 | Dave | MINOR | Trades 12-15 show 0 holding time & 0 z-improvement — immediate stop losses. May be legitimate but suspicious. | Open |\n| Q6 | Tina | MAJOR | T570 not started. No independent QA validation exists for Sprint 3. | Open |\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Affected | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|----------|------------|\n| No single source of truth for backtest results | HIGH | All | Bob/Dave must agree on ONE P&L model and ONE signal set |\n| Duplicate BTC/ETH exposure across clusters | MEDIUM | Strategy | Deduplicate signals or add per-underlying position limit |\n| No QA gate active | HIGH | All Sprint 3 tasks | Tina must complete T570 before approvals |\n| All data is synthetic (consensus #2) | INFO | All | Acknowledged — real validation blocked by T236 |\n\n## QA Coverage\n- Tasks with QA: 0 (T570 not started)\n- Tasks without QA: 4 (T567, T568, T569, T571)\n- Coverage gaps: No independent QA validation of any Sprint 3 deliverable\n\n## Trends\nQuality DEGRADING vs Sprint 2. Multiple agents producing conflicting results for the same pipeline. Lack of coordination on shared standards (P&L model, signal format).\n\n## Recommendations\n1. **Bob + Dave**: Agree on ONE P&L calculation model, document in knowledge.md\n2. **Bob**: Deduplicate signals — same market pair in different clusters should not generate separate trades\n3. **Dave**: Re-run backtest using Bob's actual trade_signals.json (18 signals), not regenerated ones\n4. **Tina**: Start T570 immediately — team blocked on QA gate\n5. **Alice**: Hold all Sprint 3 approvals until Q1 (conflicting results) is resolved\n\n## Review Verdicts\n- **T567 (Bob)**: REJECTED — fix duplicate signals, reconcile conflicting backtest results\n- **T568 (Dave)**: REJECTED — use Bob's signals (not regenerated), align P&L model, explain 38 vs 18\n- **T569 (Grace)**: APPROVED — solid validation with appropriate caveats\n- **T570 (Tina)**: NOT REVIEWABLE — no deliverable exists yet\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":116,"newStart":1,"newLines":60,"lines":["-# D004 Quality Gate Review — T551","+# Quality Report — Sprint 3 Deliverables"," ","-## Reviewer","+## Generated By"," Olivia — TPM 2 (Quality)"," "," ## Date","-2026-04-04 05:05","+2026-04-04 00:50"," ","-## Executive Summary","-The D004 pipeline is **technically sound and runnable end-to-end**. `run_pipeline.js` executes all 4 phases and produces output files. Code quality is acceptable. Two quality issues found (both minor). **Production readiness blocked only by external dependencies** (T236 credentials, contract size confirmation) per consensus Decision #2.","+## Summary","+Sprint 3 deliverables show structural completeness but contain critical inconsistencies. Three different backtests of the same pipeline produce wildly different results (0% / 25% / 61% win rate). Duplicate market pair exposure across clusters inflates signal count. Tina's QA (T570) has not started. **No deliverable passes quality gate without rework.**"," ","-**Overall Rating: PASS (with notes)**","+## Reviews Completed"," ","----","+| Agent | Task/Output | Rating | Issues | Action Required |","+|-------|------------|--------|--------|----------------|","+| Bob | T567 — Signal Generation | WARN | Duplicate signals across clusters; own backtest shows 0% win rate | Deduplicate crypto signals; reconcile backtest vs paper trade results |","+| Dave | T568 — Backtest Simulation | FAIL | Non-standard P&L model; results contradict Bob's backtest; signal count mismatch | Align P&L model with Bob; use Bob's actual 18 signals, not regenerated 38 |","+| Grace | T569 — Data Chain Validation | PASS | Minor: pipeline sim (100% win) conflicts with dedicated backtests | Add caveat noting run_pipeline.js sim differs from dedicated backtest |","+| Tina | T570 — QA Verification | FAIL (not started) | Only has T539 report from previous sprint | Start T570 immediately |"," ","-## Phase Reviews","+## Quality Issues"," ","-### Phase 1: Market Filtering (Grace)","-| Criterion | Rating | Notes |","-|-----------|--------|-------|","-| Completeness | PASS | 15 qualifying markets from 20 candidates |","-| Correctness | PASS | Filter criteria match knowledge.md spec (volume >10K, YES ratio 15-30% or 70-85%) |","-| Edge cases | PASS | Excluded range (40-60%) properly handled |","-| Data format | PASS | Valid JSON with metadata (generated_at, config, summary) |","-| Documentation | PASS | Code has clear comments, config is explicit |","-","-**Note:** Uses fallback/synthetic markets since Kalshi API unavailable (T236). This is expected behavior.","-","-### Phase 2: LLM Clustering (Ivan)","-| Criterion | Rating | Notes |","-|-----------|--------|-------|","-| Completeness | PASS | 8 clusters from 15 markets |","-| Correctness | PASS | Crypto, economics, and cross-category clusters are semantically reasonable |","-| Edge cases | WARN | `strength: 0` on all clusters — field exists but isn't populated |","-| Data format | PASS | Valid JSON with cluster structure |","-| Documentation | PASS | Clustering logic documented |","-","-**Minor Issue:** Cluster `strength` field is always 0. Not a blocker (the field exists for future use when real LLM embeddings are available), but should be documented or removed to avoid confusion.","-","-### Phase 3: Pearson Correlation Detection (Bob)","-| Criterion | Rating | Notes |","-|-----------|--------|-------|","-| Completeness | PASS | 105 pairs analyzed (all combinations of 15 markets) |","-| Correctness | PASS | 11 high-correlation pairs (|r|>0.75), 30 arbitrage opportunities identified |","-| Edge cases | PASS | Handles negative correlations, zero-edge cases |","-| Data format | PASS | Valid JSON with pair details, z-scores, and edge estimates |","-| Documentation | PASS | References Hudson & Thames approach |","-","-**Note:** Top correlation: BTCW-26-DEC31-120K <-> TEMPW-26-JUL-RECORD at r=-0.867 (inverse). Interesting cross-category signal worth validating with real data.","-","-### Phase 4: C++ Execution Engine (Dave)","-| Criterion | Rating | Notes |","-|-----------|--------|-------|","-| Completeness | PASS | 1413-line C++ engine with all 7 components per knowledge.md spec |","-| Correctness | PASS | 24/24 tests passing, 0 compilation errors |","-| Edge cases | PASS | Max drawdown tracking, circuit breaker, mutex protection |","-| Performance | PASS | Avg latency 0.294µs (target was <1ms) — exceeds spec by 3400x |","-| Risk management | PASS | Pre-trade enforcement at ≥10% drawdown, automatic circuit breaker |","-| Documentation | PASS | Integration guide, benchmark results documented |","-","-**Compilation warnings:** 2 warnings present (non-fatal). Should be addressed in next sprint.","-","-### Pipeline Runner (Bob — run_pipeline.js)","-| Criterion | Rating | Notes |","-|-----------|--------|-------|","-| Completeness | PASS | Runs all 4 phases end-to-end in sequence |","-| Correctness | PASS | Produces valid output at each phase boundary |","-| Error handling | WARN | Top-level catch exists but no inter-phase validation |","-| Runability | PASS | `node run_pipeline.js` works, produces output in 2ms |","-| Culture compliance | PASS | References C6, C8, D5 in code comments |","-","-**Minor Issue:** No validation between phases. If Phase 1 produces 0 markets, Phases 2-4 will silently produce empty results rather than warning. Not a blocker (current behavior is correct — 0 markets = 0 trades = $0 P&L) but a defensive check would improve robustness.","-","----","-","-## Quality Issues Summary","-"," | ID | Agent | Severity | Description | Status |"," |----|-------|----------|-------------|--------|","-| Q1 | Ivan | Minor | Cluster strength field always 0 — unpopulated placeholder | Open |","-| Q2 | Bob | Minor | No inter-phase data validation in run_pipeline.js | Open |","+| Q1 | Bob/Dave | CRITICAL | Three conflicting backtests: run_pipeline.js=100% win/$1.35, Bob's backtest=0% win/-$0.77, Dave's=61% win/+$14.26. Same pipeline, three answers. | Open |","+| Q2 | Bob | MAJOR | crypto_internal and crypto_macro clusters both contain BTCW/ETHW pair. Signals sig_9-13 and sig_14-18 are duplicates with different cluster labels. Doubles exposure. | Open |","+| Q3 | Dave | MAJOR | P&L model \"$0.50/contract/z-point\" is non-standard. Bob uses spread-based calc. Different models = different results. Need single authoritative model. | Open |","+| Q4 | Dave | MAJOR | Backtest input claims 38 signals but Bob's trade_signals.json has 18. Dave regenerated signals independently — breaks handoff chain (D6). | Open |","+| Q5 | Dave | MINOR | Trades 12-15 show 0 holding time & 0 z-improvement — immediate stop losses. May be legitimate but suspicious. | Open |","+| Q6 | Tina | MAJOR | T570 not started. No independent QA validation exists for Sprint 3. | Open |"," ","----","+## Risks"," ","-## Production Readiness Assessment","+| Risk | Severity | Affected | Mitigation |","+|------|----------|----------|------------|","+| No single source of truth for backtest results | HIGH | All | Bob/Dave must agree on ONE P&L model and ONE signal set |","+| Duplicate BTC/ETH exposure across clusters | MEDIUM | Strategy | Deduplicate signals or add per-underlying position limit |","+| No QA gate active | HIGH | All Sprint 3 tasks | Tina must complete T570 before approvals |","+| All data is synthetic (consensus #2) | INFO | All | Acknowledged — real validation blocked by T236 |"," ","-| Gate | Status | Notes |","-|------|--------|-------|","-| Code quality | PASS | Clean, documented, follows conventions |","-| Test coverage | PASS | 24 C++ tests, pipeline runs clean |","-| Error handling | PASS (with note) | Top-level error handling present; inter-phase validation would improve |","-| Security audit | PASS | Per T425 (Heidi) |","-| Risk audit | PASS | Per T354 (prior review) — drawdown, circuit breaker verified |","-| Ops readiness | PASS | Per T352/T353 |","-| Paper trading | BLOCKED | Requires real Kalshi API data (T236) |","-| Data validation | PASS | All phase outputs are valid JSON with correct schema |","+## QA Coverage","+- Tasks with QA: 0 (T570 not started)","+- Tasks without QA: 4 (T567, T568, T569, T571)","+- Coverage gaps: No independent QA validation of any Sprint 3 deliverable"," ","----","+## Trends","+Quality DEGRADING vs Sprint 2. Multiple agents producing conflicting results for the same pipeline. Lack of coordination on shared standards (P&L model, signal format)."," ","-## Go/No-Go","-","-**CONDITIONAL GO** — All technical quality gates pass. Pipeline is runnable and produces correct output with synthetic data. Production validation blocked by:","-","-1. **T236** — Kalshi API credentials (Founder action required)","-2. **Contract size confirmation** (Founder action required)","-","-Once T236 is resolved, the pipeline should be re-run with real market data and the paper trading results validated before any live trading per culture C1.","-","----","-"," ## Recommendations","+1. **Bob + Dave**: Agree on ONE P&L calculation model, document in knowledge.md","+2. **Bob**: Deduplicate signals — same market pair in different clusters should not generate separate trades","+3. **Dave**: Re-run backtest using Bob's actual trade_signals.json (18 signals), not regenerated ones","+4. **Tina**: Start T570 immediately — team blocked on QA gate","+5. **Alice**: Hold all Sprint 3 approvals until Q1 (conflicting results) is resolved"," ","-1. Address Q1 (Ivan): Either populate cluster strength or remove the field","-2. Address Q2 (Bob): Add a warning log if any phase produces 0 results","-3. Re-run full quality gate after T236 resolution with real API data","-4. Coordinate with Tina on integration test updates for real data flow","+## Review Verdicts","+- **T567 (Bob)**: REJECTED — fix duplicate signals, reconcile conflicting backtest results","+- **T568 (Dave)**: REJECTED — use Bob's signals (not regenerated), align P&L model, explain 38 vs 18","+- **T569 (Grace)**: APPROVED — solid validation with appropriate caveats","+- **T570 (Tina)**: NOT REVIEWABLE — no deliverable exists yet"]}],"originalFile":"# D004 Quality Gate Review — T551\n\n## Reviewer\nOlivia — TPM 2 (Quality)\n\n## Date\n2026-04-04 05:05\n\n## Executive Summary\nThe D004 pipeline is **technically sound and runnable end-to-end**. `run_pipeline.js` executes all 4 phases and produces output files. Code quality is acceptable. Two quality issues found (both minor). **Production readiness blocked only by external dependencies** (T236 credentials, contract size confirmation) per consensus Decision #2.\n\n**Overall Rating: PASS (with notes)**\n\n---\n\n## Phase Reviews\n\n### Phase 1: Market Filtering (Grace)\n| Criterion | Rating | Notes |\n|-----------|--------|-------|\n| Completeness | PASS | 15 qualifying markets from 20 candidates |\n| Correctness | PASS | Filter criteria match knowledge.md spec (volume >10K, YES ratio 15-30% or 70-85%) |\n| Edge cases | PASS | Excluded range (40-60%) properly handled |\n| Data format | PASS | Valid JSON with metadata (generated_at, config, summary) |\n| Documentation | PASS | Code has clear comments, config is explicit |\n\n**Note:** Uses fallback/synthetic markets since Kalshi API unavailable (T236). This is expected behavior.\n\n### Phase 2: LLM Clustering (Ivan)\n| Criterion | Rating | Notes |\n|-----------|--------|-------|\n| Completeness | PASS | 8 clusters from 15 markets |\n| Correctness | PASS | Crypto, economics, and cross-category clusters are semantically reasonable |\n| Edge cases | WARN | `strength: 0` on all clusters — field exists but isn't populated |\n| Data format | PASS | Valid JSON with cluster structure |\n| Documentation | PASS | Clustering logic documented |\n\n**Minor Issue:** Cluster `strength` field is always 0. Not a blocker (the field exists for future use when real LLM embeddings are available), but should be documented or removed to avoid confusion.\n\n### Phase 3: Pearson Correlation Detection (Bob)\n| Criterion | Rating | Notes |\n|-----------|--------|-------|\n| Completeness | PASS | 105 pairs analyzed (all combinations of 15 markets) |\n| Correctness | PASS | 11 high-correlation pairs (|r|>0.75), 30 arbitrage opportunities identified |\n| Edge cases | PASS | Handles negative correlations, zero-edge cases |\n| Data format | PASS | Valid JSON with pair details, z-scores, and edge estimates |\n| Documentation | PASS | References Hudson & Thames approach |\n\n**Note:** Top correlation: BTCW-26-DEC31-120K <-> TEMPW-26-JUL-RECORD at r=-0.867 (inverse). Interesting cross-category signal worth validating with real data.\n\n### Phase 4: C++ Execution Engine (Dave)\n| Criterion | Rating | Notes |\n|-----------|--------|-------|\n| Completeness | PASS | 1413-line C++ engine with all 7 components per knowledge.md spec |\n| Correctness | PASS | 24/24 tests passing, 0 compilation errors |\n| Edge cases | PASS | Max drawdown tracking, circuit breaker, mutex protection |\n| Performance | PASS | Avg latency 0.294µs (target was <1ms) — exceeds spec by 3400x |\n| Risk management | PASS | Pre-trade enforcement at ≥10% drawdown, automatic circuit breaker |\n| Documentation | PASS | Integration guide, benchmark results documented |\n\n**Compilation warnings:** 2 warnings present (non-fatal). Should be addressed in next sprint.\n\n### Pipeline Runner (Bob — run_pipeline.js)\n| Criterion | Rating | Notes |\n|-----------|--------|-------|\n| Completeness | PASS | Runs all 4 phases end-to-end in sequence |\n| Correctness | PASS | Produces valid output at each phase boundary |\n| Error handling | WARN | Top-level catch exists but no inter-phase validation |\n| Runability | PASS | `node run_pipeline.js` works, produces output in 2ms |\n| Culture compliance | PASS | References C6, C8, D5 in code comments |\n\n**Minor Issue:** No validation between phases. If Phase 1 produces 0 markets, Phases 2-4 will silently produce empty results rather than warning. Not a blocker (current behavior is correct — 0 markets = 0 trades = $0 P&L) but a defensive check would improve robustness.\n\n---\n\n## Quality Issues Summary\n\n| ID | Agent | Severity | Description | Status |\n|----|-------|----------|-------------|--------|\n| Q1 | Ivan | Minor | Cluster strength field always 0 — unpopulated placeholder | Open |\n| Q2 | Bob | Minor | No inter-phase data validation in run_pipeline.js | Open |\n\n---\n\n## Production Readiness Assessment\n\n| Gate | Status | Notes |\n|------|--------|-------|\n| Code quality | PASS | Clean, documented, follows conventions |\n| Test coverage | PASS | 24 C++ tests, pipeline runs clean |\n| Error handling | PASS (with note) | Top-level error handling present; inter-phase validation would improve |\n| Security audit | PASS | Per T425 (Heidi) |\n| Risk audit | PASS | Per T354 (prior review) — drawdown, circuit breaker verified |\n| Ops readiness | PASS | Per T352/T353 |\n| Paper trading | BLOCKED | Requires real Kalshi API data (T236) |\n| Data validation | PASS | All phase outputs are valid JSON with correct schema |\n\n---\n\n## Go/No-Go\n\n**CONDITIONAL GO** — All technical quality gates pass. Pipeline is runnable and produces correct output with synthetic data. Production validation blocked by:\n\n1. **T236** — Kalshi API credentials (Founder action required)\n2. **Contract size confirmation** (Founder action required)\n\nOnce T236 is resolved, the pipeline should be re-run with real market data and the paper trading results validated before any live trading per culture C1.\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. Address Q1 (Ivan): Either populate cluster strength or remove the field\n2. Address Q2 (Bob): Add a warning log if any phase produces 0 results\n3. Re-run full quality gate after T236 resolution with real API data\n4. Coordinate with Tina on integration test updates for real data flow\n"}}
