{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SqtGX4HPFjk6eNkHeQqqQL","type":"tool_result","content":"# T582 Ready for Review — Credential Manager\n\n**From:** Bob (Backend Engineer)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nT582 (Credential management & API key security) is ready for review.\n\n**Deliverable:** `output/credential_manager.js` + `output/shared/codebase/backend/credential_manager.js`\n**Run:** `node credential_manager.js` (validates credentials, shows audit log with `--audit`)\n\n**Features:**\n1. .env file loader (zero dependencies) — loads KALSHI_API_KEY, KALSHI_API_SECRET, KALSHI_EMAIL, KALSHI_PASSWORD\n2. Credential validation — checks auth method configured before pipeline starts\n3. Rate limiter — 10 req/s trading, 100 req/s data (Kalshi API limits)\n4. Audit logger — JSONL log of all credential loads, validations, API calls\n5. .gitignore enforcement — auto-adds .env, .env.*, audit_log.jsonl\n6. Paper trading default (C1) — PAPER_TRADING=false requires explicit opt-in\n7. Integrates with kalshi_client.js via `createClient()` method\n\nFollowing C11 (review before done), C5 (task progression).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d95e38b3-86a2-4243-a4c0-b8edce7e0010","uuid":"54ba72bc-1215-477e-b59b-10a3fb277134","timestamp":"2026-04-04T20:04:15.508Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# T582 Ready for Review — Credential Manager\n\n**From:** Bob (Backend Engineer)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nT582 (Credential management & API key security) is ready for review.\n\n**Deliverable:** `output/credential_manager.js` + `output/shared/codebase/backend/credential_manager.js`\n**Run:** `node credential_manager.js` (validates credentials, shows audit log with `--audit`)\n\n**Features:**\n1. .env file loader (zero dependencies) — loads KALSHI_API_KEY, KALSHI_API_SECRET, KALSHI_EMAIL, KALSHI_PASSWORD\n2. Credential validation — checks auth method configured before pipeline starts\n3. Rate limiter — 10 req/s trading, 100 req/s data (Kalshi API limits)\n4. Audit logger — JSONL log of all credential loads, validations, API calls\n5. .gitignore enforcement — auto-adds .env, .env.*, audit_log.jsonl\n6. Paper trading default (C1) — PAPER_TRADING=false requires explicit opt-in\n7. Integrates with kalshi_client.js via `createClient()` method\n\nFollowing C11 (review before done), C5 (task progression).","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
